BT 1 0 0 1 0 104 Tm .631906 Tw 14.2 TL /F1 9.6 Tf .105882 .117647 .141176 rg (Through 2025 and into 2026, bug bounty programs were flooded with \223AI slop\224 \227 LLM-generated reports that read) Tj T* 0 Tw .133835 Tw (convincingly but describe vulnerabilities that do not exist, cite functions that aren't real, and can't be reproduced. The) Tj T* 0 Tw .384914 Tw (curl project reported that roughly a fifth of its 2025 submissions were AI slop while genuine ones fell to about one in) Tj T* 0 Tw .8832 Tw (twenty, and it paused its long-running bug bounty in early 2026 before resuming once report quality recovered. Its) Tj T* 0 Tw .246857 Tw (maintainer's bar is blunt: if you cannot explain a bug in a few sentences and reproduce it, do not submit it. Platforms) Tj T* 0 Tw .48 Tw (adapted too \227 HackerOne framed 2025 as the rise of the \223bionic hacker,\224 with valid AI-assisted findings up sharply) Tj T* 0 Tw .954133 Tw (year over year and an AI assistant \(its Hai agent\) now pre-checking reports for scope and completeness before a) Tj T* 0 Tw (human reviews them.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
q
1 0 0 1 57.84 179.96 cm
q
BT 1 0 0 1 0 47.2 Tm 1.356424 Tw 14.2 TL /F1 9.6 Tf .105882 .117647 .141176 rg (The same stretch proved the flip side. AI wielded by skilled humans found real, novel vulnerabilities \227 including) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.5732 Tw (genuine CVEs in curl and a batch of previously unknown OpenSSL issues \227 that careful operators responsibly) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.10176 Tw (disclosed. In short, AI collapsed the ) Tj /F3 9.6 Tf (median) Tj /F1 9.6 Tf ( report quality while raising the ) Tj /F3 9.6 Tf (ceiling) Tj /F1 9.6 Tf (. Which side of that split you land on) Tj T* 0 Tw (is a choice you make on every single submission.) Tj T* ET
